==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: groat
<hw>groat</hw> <pr>(gr⟦add⟧t <it>or</it> gr⟦omac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[LG. <ets>gr⟦omac⟧te</ets>, orig., great, that is, a great piece of
coin, larger than other coins in former use. See <er>Great</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An old English silver coin, equal to four
pence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any small sum of money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groats</ent>⟦br⟧
